(590, 212, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:11:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:4:\"1500\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:4:\"1200\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"7\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"6\";s:10:\"trip_facts\";a:4:{s:8:\"field_id\";a:2:{i:1;s:14:\"transportation\";i:3;s:8:\"altitude\";}s:10:\"field_type\";a:2:{i:1;s:4:\"text\";i:3;s:4:\"text\";}i:1;a:1:{i:1;s:11:\"1-12 people\";}i:3;a:1:{i:3;s:8:\"Moderate\";}}s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:7:{i:1;s:39:\"Chandigarh – Shimla (140 Kms 3-4 Hrs)\";i:2;s:40:\"Shimla- Rampur-Sarahan (163 Kms 4-5 Hrs)\";i:3;s:31:\"Sarahan -Kalpa (98 Kms 3-4 Hrs)\";i:4;s:29:\"Kalpa-Sangla (40 Kms 1-2 Hrs)\";i:5;s:6:\"Sangla\";i:6;s:34:\"Sangla to Shimla (240 Kms 7-8 Hrs)\";i:7;s:39:\"Shimla – Chandigarh (140 Kms 3-4 Hrs)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:7:{i:1;s:253:\"Arrival Chandigarh airport/railway station &amp; meet our assisted driver and transfer to Shimla. Arrival Shimla check in to the hotel &amp; Evening free to stroll in the famous the mall &amp; The Ridge and back to the hotel, overnight stay in the hotel\";i:2;s:354:\"Travel by road from Shimla to Sarahan, the gateway to Kinnaur Enroute crossing the famous hill resorts of Kufri &amp; Narkanda. Enroute also visit Rampur and view padam palace. Continue drive along the Sutluj River and from jeori climb up to Sarahan. On arrival check in at hotel, Evening visit the famous Bhimakali temple at Sarahan, Overnight at hotel.\";i:3;s:355:\"After breakfast travel by surface from Sarahan to Kalpa The route is along the Sutlej River. Kalpa is a beautiful village located in the back drop of Kinner Kailash .Mountain range .On arrival check in at hotel ,afternoon visit Roghi village which has traditionally built Kinnauri houses ,evening free to walk around the Kalpa village ,Overnight at hotel.\";i:4;s:338:\"After breakfast proceed to Sangla which has earned distinction of one of the most beautiful valleys in Himachal. At Sangla visit Kamru village and make a small walk to visit kamru Fort which has a temple dedicated to Kamaksha Devi. &amp; Check in at Camp rest of day is free to relax and enjoy the pristine beauty. Overnight stay at Camp.\";i:5;s:182:\"After breakfast an excursion visiting the picturesque village of Chitkul. Drive back to Sangla, rest of Day free to relax or make walks to nearby bastseri village .Overnight at camp.\";i:6;s:95:\"Travel by surface from Sangla to Shimla .On arrival check in at hotel .Overnight stay at hotel.\";i:7;s:129:\"In time transfer to Kalka station or Chandigarh airport/railway station for onward destination end of our tour &amp; Our Service.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:7:{i:1;s:272:\"&lt;p&gt;Arrival Chandigarh airport/railway station &amp; meet our assisted driver and transfer to Shimla. Arrival Shimla check in to the hotel &amp; Evening free to stroll in the famous the mall &amp; The Ridge and back to the hotel, overnight stay in the hotel&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:373:\"&lt;p&gt;Travel by road from Shimla to Sarahan, the gateway to Kinnaur Enroute crossing the famous hill resorts of Kufri &amp; Narkanda. Enroute also visit Rampur and view padam palace. Continue drive along the Sutluj River and from jeori climb up to Sarahan. On arrival check in at hotel, Evening visit the famous Bhimakali temple at Sarahan, Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:374:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast travel by surface from Sarahan to Kalpa The route is along the Sutlej River. Kalpa is a beautiful village located in the back drop of Kinner Kailash .Mountain range .On arrival check in at hotel ,afternoon visit Roghi village which has traditionally built Kinnauri houses ,evening free to walk around the Kalpa village ,Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:357:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast proceed to Sangla which has earned distinction of one of the most beautiful valleys in Himachal. At Sangla visit Kamru village and make a small walk to visit kamru Fort which has a temple dedicated to Kamaksha Devi. &amp; Check in at Camp rest of day is free to relax and enjoy the pristine beauty. Overnight stay at Camp.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:201:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast an excursion visiting the picturesque village of Chitkul. Drive back to Sangla, rest of Day free to relax or make walks to nearby bastseri village .Overnight at camp.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:114:\"&lt;p&gt;Travel by surface from Sangla to Shimla .On arrival check in at hotel .Overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:7;s:148:\"&lt;p&gt;In time transfer to Kalka station or Chandigarh airport/railway station for onward destination end of our tour &amp; Our Service.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:346:\"Chandigarh – Shimla - Cab Tour\r\nNon Ac Cab for Manali with Shimla, Sarahan, Kalpa ,Sangla  Tour\r\n Hotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.\r\n 02 night accommodation in Shimla.\r\n 01 night accommodation in Sarahan.\r\n 01 night accommodation in Kalpa.\r\n 02 night accommodation in Sangla Camp.\r\n All taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:500:\"&lt;li&gt;Chandigarh – Shimla - Cab Tour&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Non Ac Cab for Manali with Shimla, Sarahan, Kalpa ,Sangla  Tour&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; Hotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; 02 night accommodation in Shimla.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; 01 night accommodation in Sarahan.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; 01 night accommodation in Kalpa.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; 02 night accommodation in Sangla Camp.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; All taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:198:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees\r\nGuide /Entertainment fee\r\nAny which is not mention in above package cost\r\nAny Guide fees/entrainment fees\r\nAny Air and Train fare\r\nGovt. service tax 4.50% extra\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:314:\"&lt;li&gt;Monuments entry fees and camera fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide /Entertainment fee&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any which is not mention in above package cost&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Guide fees/entrainment fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Air and Train fare&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Govt. service tax 4.50% extra&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
