(596, 254, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:11:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:4:\"1700\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:4:\"1200\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"8\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"7\";s:10:\"trip_facts\";a:4:{s:8:\"field_id\";a:2:{i:1;s:14:\"transportation\";i:3;s:8:\"altitude\";}s:10:\"field_type\";a:2:{i:1;s:4:\"text\";i:3;s:4:\"text\";}i:1;a:1:{i:1;s:11:\"1-12 people\";}i:3;a:1:{i:3;s:8:\"Moderate\";}}s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:38:\"CHANDIGARH TO SHIMLA (115 KMS 3-4 hrs)\";i:2;s:24:\"SHIMLA- SIGHTSEENG-KUFRI\";i:3;s:35:\"SHIMLA TO SARAHAN (163 KMS 4-5 hrs)\";i:4;s:34:\"SARAHAN TO SANGLA (97 KMS 3-4 hrs)\";i:5;s:9:\"IN SANGLA\";i:6;s:32:\"SANGLA TO KALPA (40 KMS 1-2 hrs)\";i:7;s:33:\"KALPA TO SHIMLA (241 KMS 7-8 hrs)\";i:8;s:38:\"SHIMLA TO CHANDIGARH (115 KMS 3-4 hrs)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:150:\"On Arrival Chandigarh you will meet our representative and drive for Shimla. Arrival Shimla you check into the hotel, dinner, overnight stay at hotel.\";i:2;s:663:\"This day after breakfast check out from the hotel proceed for in and around sightseeing of SHIMLA, visit KUFRI, India\'s one of the best holiday paradise Kufri in Shimla is beautifully tucked on an altitude of 2,622 meter. The place is a tourist hotspot for its awesome scenic and sports activities. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – &quot;THE MALL &amp; THE RIDGE&quot; This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla\'s landmarks - the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo - Tudor library building - are worth seeing. Dinner and overnight stay in the hotel.....\";i:3;s:254:\"Morning after breakfast check out the hotel drive from Shimla to Sarahan enroute visiting Sun temple at Nirath Rampur. On arrival check in at hotel. Evening visit Bhimakali temple which is one of the 51 shaktipeeths of Hindu religion. Overnight at hotel.\";i:4;s:147:\"After breakfast check out the hotel drive for Sangla valley. On arrival check in Hotel. Rest of the day free. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.\";i:5;s:120:\"Morning after breakfast drive for a sightseeing visit Rackham and Chitkul village. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.\";i:6;s:198:\"Morning after breakfasts check out the hotel &amp; visit Kamru village, fort and later continue drive to kalpa. On arrival check in hotel. Rest of the day free. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.\";i:7;s:110:\"Morning after breakfast drive back to Shimla. On arrival check in at hotel. Rest at hotel. Overnight at hotel.\";i:8;s:151:\"After breakfast check out the hotel and Drive for Chandigarh. And drop at Chandigarh Airport/ Railway Station. And end of our service and your journey.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:8:{i:1;s:169:\"&lt;p&gt;On Arrival Chandigarh you will meet our representative and drive for Shimla. Arrival Shimla you check into the hotel, dinner, overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:682:\"&lt;p&gt;This day after breakfast check out from the hotel proceed for in and around sightseeing of SHIMLA, visit KUFRI, India\'s one of the best holiday paradise Kufri in Shimla is beautifully tucked on an altitude of 2,622 meter. The place is a tourist hotspot for its awesome scenic and sports activities. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – &quot;THE MALL &amp; THE RIDGE&quot; This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla\'s landmarks - the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo - Tudor library building - are worth seeing. Dinner and overnight stay in the hotel.....&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:273:\"&lt;p&gt;Morning after breakfast check out the hotel drive from Shimla to Sarahan enroute visiting Sun temple at Nirath Rampur. On arrival check in at hotel. Evening visit Bhimakali temple which is one of the 51 shaktipeeths of Hindu religion. Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:166:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast check out the hotel drive for Sangla valley. On arrival check in Hotel. Rest of the day free. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:139:\"&lt;p&gt;Morning after breakfast drive for a sightseeing visit Rackham and Chitkul village. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:217:\"&lt;p&gt;Morning after breakfasts check out the hotel &amp; visit Kamru village, fort and later continue drive to kalpa. On arrival check in hotel. Rest of the day free. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:7;s:129:\"&lt;p&gt;Morning after breakfast drive back to Shimla. On arrival check in at hotel. Rest at hotel. Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:8;s:170:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast check out the hotel and Drive for Chandigarh. And drop at Chandigarh Airport/ Railway Station. And end of our service and your journey.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:347:\"Entire Round Trip ex Chandigarh by Cab.\r\nNon Ac Cab for Local Sightseeing Shimla, Sarahan, Sangla, Kalpa.\r\nHotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.\r\n03 nights\' accommodation in Shimla.\r\n01 night accommodation in Sarahan.\r\n02 nights\' accommodation in Sangla.\r\n01 night accommodation in Kalpa.\r\nAll taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:501:\"&lt;li&gt;Entire Round Trip ex Chandigarh by Cab.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Non Ac Cab for Local Sightseeing Shimla, Sarahan, Sangla, Kalpa.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;03 nights\' accommodation in Shimla.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Sarahan.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;02 nights\' accommodation in Sangla.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Kalpa.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:198:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees\r\nGuide /Entertainment fee\r\nAny which is not mention in above package cost\r\nAny Guide fees/entrainment fees\r\nAny Air and Train fare\r\nGovt. service tax 4.50% extra\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:314:\"&lt;li&gt;Monuments entry fees and camera fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide /Entertainment fee&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any which is not mention in above package cost&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Guide fees/entrainment fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Air and Train fare&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Govt. service tax 4.50% extra&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
