ep ridges on the left bank of Spiti River. Today Visit the Ki monastery. It is the oldest and the biggest monastery of Spiti dominating Ki-Village. After that visit Kibber village. In the afternoon, travel to Tashigong village to see the La darcha Fair grounds and the Chao Kang Nilda peak.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:554:\"&lt;p&gt;This day after breakfast visit the Dhankar and Taboo monasteries. Dhankar Monastery is above the Dhankar Village, between the Kaza and Taboo. Dhanker means &quot;Fort on Cliff&quot;. The complex is built on a 1000-foot (300-metre) high spur overlooking the confluence of the Spiti and Pin Rivers. After that proceed to Taboo. Taboo Monastery known as Ajanta of the Himalayas. Taboo monastery is more than a thousand years old and is famous for its wall paintings and murals. It is also known as the. Return back to Kaza in the evening.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:519:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast checkout hotel and proceed from Kaza to Sissu. On the way you can cover Chandertal. The name of the lake originates from its crescent shape. It is situated at an altitude of about 4,300 metres (14,100 ft) in the Himalayas. After that proceed to Lahaul. You can take your lunch at Chatru or Khoksar. Khoksar is the first village of Lahaul. On arrival at Sissu check in hotel.In the evening you can visit Sissu Lake and Raja Geypen Temple, the powerful presiding deity of Lahaul valley.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:7;s:916:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast proceed to Udaipur. On the way you can visit Gondhla, s located on the river bank of the river Chandra. House of the Thakur of Gondhla, called Gondhla castle or fort, is the main attraction. Tandi is situated at the confluence of Chandra and Bhaga rivers. Tandi\'s importance for the people of Lahaul is same as it is \'Haridwar\' for the Hindus. In Tandi you can visit Tupchiling Monastery and ancient Guru Gantal monastery. After that travel to Udaipur, located in the Patten valley. A beautiful side valley in Lahaul. Udaipur and Triloknath Temple are the famous place in Lahoul. Trilokinath is famous for the Shiva temple. This is holy shrine is revered equally by Hindus and the Buddhists and Udaipur is known for the ancient Marikula Mata temple. In the evening, explore the Udaipur village and visit the Mrikula Devi. Overnight in Udaipur.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:8;s:544:\"&lt;p&gt;Travel to Keylong the headquarters of Lahaul. On the way visit Yordong Monastery, Located on Manali Leh Highway in a place called Beeling, near to the head quarter Keylong. On arrival at Keylong check in hotel. After fresh up visit Shashur Monastery and explore in Keylong market. After that hike up to the Khardong village and monastery. Kardang Monastery or Gompa is a famous Drukpa Linage Monastery and is the most important monastery Lahoul valley, India. The associated village of Kardang was once the capital of Lahaul.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:9;s:172:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast early in the morning drive to Manali. In Manali after fresh up drop at Volvo bus point. Proceed to Delhi with sweet memories of the trip.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:357:\"Delhi – Manali- Delhi Volvo Tickets.\r\nNon Ac Cab for Manali with Lahaul Spiti Tour.\r\nHotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.\r\n01 night accommodation in Manali.\r\n03 night accommodation in Kaza.\r\n01 night accommodation in Sissu.\r\n01 night accommodation in Udaipur.\r\n01 night accommodation in Keylong.\r\nAll taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:530:\"&lt;li&gt;Delhi – Manali- Delhi Volvo Tickets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Non Ac Cab for Manali with Lahaul Spiti Tour.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hotel Accommodation with breakfast and dinner.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Manali.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;03 night accommodation in Kaza.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Sissu.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Udaipur.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;01 night accommodation in Keylong.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All taxes are included except Govt. Service Tax.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:198:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees\r\nGuide /Entertainment fee\r\nAny which is not mention in above package cost\r\nAny Guide fees/entrainment fees\r\nAny Air and Train fare\r\nGovt. service tax 4.50% extra\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:314:\"&lt;li&gt;Monuments entry fees and camera fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Guide /Entertainment fee&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any which is not mention in above package cost&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Guide fees/entrainment fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Air and Train fare&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Govt. service tax 4.50% extra&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
