(685, 269, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:11:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:4:\"1299\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:4:\"9999\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"6\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"5\";s:10:\"trip_facts\";a:4:{s:8:\"field_id\";a:2:{i:1;s:14:\"transportation\";i:3;s:8:\"altitude\";}s:10:\"field_type\";a:2:{i:1;s:4:\"text\";i:3;s:4:\"text\";}i:1;a:1:{i:1;s:11:\"1-12 people\";}i:3;a:1:{i:3;s:8:\"Moderate\";}}s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:6:{i:1;s:38:\"Delhi – Shimla ( 400 Kmtrs 9-10 hrs)\";i:2;s:34:\"Shimla-Kufri sight seeing -Shimla.\";i:3;s:33:\"Shimla-Manali (265 kmtrs 7-8 hrs)\";i:4;s:36:\"Manali-Rohtangpass (Up to snow line)\";i:5;s:24:\"Manali Town Sight seeing\";i:6;s:48:\"Manali – Delhi Departure (570 kmtrs 13-14 hrs)\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:6:{i:1;s:366:\"On arrival at Delhi Airport / Railway Station and you will be met, assisted and drive to Shimla (located 380kms). Shimla was the former summer capital of British India, set amidst the snow capped Shivalik Mountains. which offers some of the most stunning views of the mighty Himalayas. On arrival at Shimla check in at the hotel. Overnight in Shimla.(8 hrs Journey).\";i:2;s:618:\"This day after breakfast proceed for in and around sightseeing of SHIMLA, visit KUFRI, India’s one of the best holiday paradise Kufri in Shimla is beautifully tucked on an altitude of 2,622 meter. The place is a tourist hotspot for its awesome scenic and sports activities. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – “THE MALL &amp; THE RIDGE” This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla’s landmarks – the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo – Tudor library building – are worth seeing. Overnight at hotel.\";i:3;s:218:\"After breakfast leave for Manali,on the way sight-seeing like Sundernagar lake,Pandoh dam, Hanogi Mata &amp; Vaishno Devi Temple and Kullu Valley on arrival in Manali check in hotel,dinner and overnight stay in Manali.\";i:4;s:469:\"Excursion to Rohatang Pass. Situated at an altitude of 3979 mtrs above sea level and 51 kms outside Manali is the mighty Rohtang Pass – the gateway to Lahaul-Spiti valley. It affords a wide panoramic view of the mountains. Here one sees the majesty of the mountains at its height and splendor. At the top of the pass the air seems to glitter against the snow as you look down over herringboned ridges into the Lahaul valley. Dinner at hotel over night stay in Manali.\";i:5;s:526:\"Half Day local sightseeing of Manali “HADIMBA TEMPLE” Built in 1553 with a superbly crafted four tiered pagoda roof, it is famous for its exquisitely carved doorway . “CLUB HOUSE” The Club House with its comprehensive facilities that include a roller skating rink, an auditorium, billiards rooms, a library, a bar and restaurant makes wonderful outing for the day.” Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar, and “VASHIST” Well known for its hot springs. There are old temples dedicated to the sage Vashisth and to Lord Rama.\";i:6;s:127:\"After having breakfast leave for Delhi drop at Railway station/Airport to catch onwards train/flight for respected destiantion.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:6:{i:1;s:385:\"&lt;p&gt;On arrival at Delhi Airport / Railway Station and you will be met, assisted and drive to Shimla (located 380kms). Shimla was the former summer capital of British India, set amidst the snow capped Shivalik Mountains. which offers some of the most stunning views of the mighty Himalayas. On arrival at Shimla check in at the hotel. Overnight in Shimla.(8 hrs Journey).&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:637:\"&lt;p&gt;This day after breakfast proceed for in and around sightseeing of SHIMLA, visit KUFRI, India’s one of the best holiday paradise Kufri in Shimla is beautifully tucked on an altitude of 2,622 meter. The place is a tourist hotspot for its awesome scenic and sports activities. Evening free to stroll in the famous shopping place of Shimla town – “THE MALL &amp; THE RIDGE” This large open space in the heart of town presents excellent views of the mountain ranges. Shimla’s landmarks – the neo- gothic structure of Christ Church and the neo – Tudor library building – are worth seeing. Overnight at hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:237:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast leave for Manali,on the way sight-seeing like Sundernagar lake,Pandoh dam, Hanogi Mata &amp; Vaishno Devi Temple and Kullu Valley on arrival in Manali check in hotel,dinner and overnight stay in Manali.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:488:\"&lt;p&gt;Excursion to Rohatang Pass. Situated at an altitude of 3979 mtrs above sea level and 51 kms outside Manali is the mighty Rohtang Pass – the gateway to Lahaul-Spiti valley. It affords a wide panoramic view of the mountains. Here one sees the majesty of the mountains at its height and splendor. At the top of the pass the air seems to glitter against the snow as you look down over herringboned ridges into the Lahaul valley. Dinner at hotel over night stay in Manali.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:546:\"&lt;p&gt;Half Day local sightseeing of Manali “HADIMBA TEMPLE” Built in 1553 with a superbly crafted four tiered pagoda roof, it is famous for its exquisitely carved doorway . “CLUB HOUSE” The Club House with its comprehensive facilities that include a roller skating rink, an auditorium, billiards rooms, a library, a bar and restaurant makes wonderful outing for the day.” Tibetan Monastery, Van Vihar, and “VASHIST” Well known for its hot springs. There are old temples dedicated to the sage Vashisth and to Lord Rama. &lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:146:\"&lt;p&gt;After having breakfast leave for Delhi drop at Railway station/Airport to catch onwards train/flight for respected destiantion.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Includes\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:445:\"Transportation by Non AC Indigo Car (2 Pax) OR Tavera (4 Pax &amp; 6 Pax) for the entire tour.\r\nAll sightseeing and excursion as per the itinerary.\r\nMentioned or similar hotels on MAP (Breakfast and Dinner Basis).\r\nIndigo AC Supplement Cost 1,500/- Innova AC Supplement Cost 2,500/- .\r\nInclusive of all the applicable Taxes except Govt service tax of 3.50 %.\r\nInclusive of Toll Tax, Parking, Driver allowance, State tax, Luxury Tax, Service Tax.\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:561:\"&lt;li&gt;Transportation by Non AC Indigo Car (2 Pax) OR Tavera (4 Pax &amp; 6 Pax) for the entire tour.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All sightseeing and excursion as per the itinerary.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mentioned or similar hotels on MAP (Breakfast and Dinner Basis).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Indigo AC Supplement Cost 1,500/- Innova AC Supplement Cost 2,500/- .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inclusive of all the applicable Taxes except Govt service tax of 3.50 %.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Inclusive of Toll Tax, Parking, Driver allowance, State tax, Luxury Tax, Service Tax.&lt;/li&gt;\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:22:\"The Trip Cost Excludes\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:199:\"Monuments entry fees and camera fees.\r\nAny which is not mentioned in above package cost.\r\nAny Guide fees/entertainment fees\r\nAny Air and train fare\r\nGovt. service tax 4.5% Extra in each tour Packages\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:296:\"&lt;li&gt;Monuments entry fees and camera fees.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any which is not mentioned in above package cost.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Guide fees/entertainment fees&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any Air and train fare&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Govt. service tax 4.5% Extra in each tour Packages&lt;/li&gt;\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Frequently asked Questions\";s:9:\"faq_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:40:\"How fit do I need to be to do this trek?\";i:2;s:70:\"How long do we walk every day when doing Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:3;s:50:\"What is the highest altitude reached in this trek?\";i:4;s:54:\"What about battery charging and hot shower facilities?\";i:5;s:49:\"Are there ATMs on the way to Annapurna Base Camp?\";i:6;s:27:\"What about internet access?\";i:7;s:80:\"Is it necessary to hire Guides/trekking agency for Annapurna Base Camp trekking?\";i:8;s:36:\"How much do guides and porters cost?\";}s:11:\"faq_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:265:\"Annapurna Base Camp is a Grade B or a moderately difficult trekking route. So any fit person can do this trek, even if you do not have any previous experience. You should be aware of what to expect and mentally prepare for it. Then, as long as you will to, you can.\";i:2;s:131:\"On average, you walk about 4 to 6 hours per day. One or two days can be as less as 3hrs and one or two days can be as long as 7hrs.\";i:3;s:131:\"The highest altitude reached is 4190m. This is the elevation of Annapurna Base Camp. ABC is the highest we will climb in this trek.\";i:4;s:230:\"Yes, you can charge batteries en route. Charger should be brought. There are hot shower facilities as well. You may have to pay certain amount for both ($1-$2). Negotiate. Also, hot water facility could be free at lower elevation.\";i:5;s:240:\"No. There are no ATMs on this trek route. You will have to draw enough cash in Pokhara or Kathmandu. There are a number of ATMs in these cities. Everything is paid in Nepali rupees. So money should be exchanged before the start of the trek.\";i:6;s:191:\"Yes. Internet can be accessed in most places. Sometimes, there might be some technical problems. Internet in Nepal is not as fast as you are used to and at times you can just lose connection.\";i:7;s:547:\"Not really. It depends on you. If you want, ABC trekking can be done independently. You could hire a guide and a porter by yourself instead of going through an agency or not hire a guide at all. Although, not having a guide can be a little problematic during off season.\r\n\r\nIt really depends on you. Is it your first time in Nepal? How confident are you of being able to find your way around? How pressed on time are you? If you go through an agency, it will be costlier but everything will be planned. You will only have to come, trek and return.\";i:8;s:103:\"For Annapurna region, pay for guides range from $20 to $30 per day and porters take $15 to $25 per day.\";}}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
