(1705, 694, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:10:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:5:\"18999\";s:4:\"sale\";s:1:\"1\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:5:\"13999\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"6\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"5\";s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:6:{i:1;s:15:\"Leh – Arrival\";i:2;s:25:\"Leh – Local Sightseeing\";i:3;s:49:\"Leh – Khardongla Top 18,390Ft. – Nubra Valley\";i:4;s:44:\"Nubra Valley- Khardongla Top- 18,390 Ft -Leh\";i:5;s:28:\"Leh – Pangong Lake – Leh\";i:6;s:12:\"Leh – Drop\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:6:{i:1;s:338:\"On arrival, our representative(s) arrange for the transfer to your hotel. Check into the hotel and use the rest of the day to rest and get acclimatized to the high altitude (3500 meters/11800 ft) and low air pressure in Leh. Strolling around the local markets maybe a good idea during the evening. Overnight stay is arranged at the Hotel.\";i:2;s:264:\"Post Breakfast we proceed for Indus Valley Monastery tour including Shey, The ancient capital of Ladakh, Thiksey an impressive complex rising tier upon tier on a hill above the village, Stok Palace &amp; Sindhu Ghat. Evening come back to hotel. Overnight at Hotel.\";i:3;s:615:\"Post breakfast we drive to Khardongla, over Khardung La (One of The Highest Motorable Road In The World) at 5,602 Mtrs /18,390 Ft, around 39 km from Leh. From the pass, one can see all the way south over the Indus valley to seemingly endless peaks and ridges of the Zanskar range,and north to the giants of the Saser massif. Upon arrival in Khardong la group will spend some time over there &amp; then drive to nubra Valley, enroute visit Deskit monastery, Evening arrive at Nubra Valley. Visit Hundar &amp; Sand dunes. you can take ride of double humped camel there. Check into the hotel/camp &amp; overnight stay.\";i:4;s:90:\"Post breakfast we shall drive back to Leh, Check into the hotel/camp &amp; overnight stay.\";i:5;s:376:\"In the early morning of the penultimate day, an excursion is scheduled to Pangong Lake, a 135 km drive from Leh. The Pangong Lake is 140km long and 3-5km in width – more than half of which lies in Tibetan territory. As you return back Leh by evening, you can use the remaining time exploring local markets, looking for a decent bargain. Overnight stay is again at the hotel.\";i:6;s:73:\"Early morning transfer to KBR airport to board flight for onward journey.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:6:{i:1;s:396:\"&lt;p&gt;On arrival, our representative(s) arrange for the transfer to your hotel. Check into the hotel and use the rest of the day to rest and get acclimatized to the high altitude (3500 meters/11800 ft) and low air pressure in Leh. Strolling around the local markets maybe a good idea during the evening. Overnight stay is arranged at the Hotel. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:283:\"&lt;p&gt;Post Breakfast we proceed for Indus Valley Monastery tour including Shey, The ancient capital of Ladakh, Thiksey an impressive complex rising tier upon tier on a hill above the village, Stok Palace &amp; Sindhu Ghat. Evening come back to hotel. Overnight at Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:634:\"&lt;p&gt;Post breakfast we drive to Khardongla, over Khardung La (One of The Highest Motorable Road In The World) at 5,602 Mtrs /18,390 Ft, around 39 km from Leh. From the pass, one can see all the way south over the Indus valley to seemingly endless peaks and ridges of the Zanskar range,and north to the giants of the Saser massif. Upon arrival in Khardong la group will spend some time over there &amp; then drive to nubra Valley, enroute visit Deskit monastery, Evening arrive at Nubra Valley. Visit Hundar &amp; Sand dunes. you can take ride of double humped camel there. Check into the hotel/camp &amp; overnight stay.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:109:\"&lt;p&gt;Post breakfast we shall drive back to Leh, Check into the hotel/camp &amp; overnight stay.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s