(1761, 703, 'wp_travel_engine_setting', 'a:9:{s:15:\"trip_prev_price\";s:5:\"20999\";s:10:\"trip_price\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"trip_duration\";s:1:\"8\";s:20:\"trip_duration_nights\";s:1:\"7\";s:11:\"tab_content\";a:2:{s:10:\"1_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"map_wpeditor\";s:0:\"\";}s:9:\"itinerary\";a:3:{s:15:\"itinerary_title\";a:8:{i:1;s:36:\"Jammu Arrival-Katra (50 Km, 2-3 Hrs)\";i:2;s:42:\"Katra ​- Ma Vaishano Devi Darshan- Katra\";i:3;s:44:\"Katra – Patnitop- Pahalgam (360 km. 8 hrs)\";i:4;s:48:\"Pahalgam -Sightseeing– Srinagar (90 km. 2 hrs)\";i:5;s:27:\"Srinagar- Local Sightseeing\";i:6;s:36:\"Srinagar – Gulmarg -Srinagar (150)\";i:7;s:47:\"Srinagar – Sonmarg –Srinagar (80 km. 2 hrs)\";i:8;s:17:\"Srinagar Dropping\";}s:17:\"itinerary_content\";a:8:{i:1;s:566:\"On arrival at Jammu Airport/Railway Station you will meet and greet with our representative and derive for Katra, situated in the foothills of Trikuta Mountains where the holy shrine of Mata Vaishno Rani is located. In Katra Check in hotel, dinner and overnight stay in hotel. Day: 02) Vaishno Devi Darshan-Katra After breakfast at hotel and proceed for Darshan here you will be guided and escorted towards Mata Vaishno Devi shrine for traditional ritual and belief and fulfill your cultural chastity. After Darshan you will be back towards hotel for Overnight stay.\";i:2;s:261:\"After breakfast at hotel and proceed for Darshan here you will be guided and escorted towards Mata Vaishno Devi shrine for traditional ritual and belief and fulfill your cultural chastity.After Darshan you will be back towards hotel for ​O​vernight stay.​\";i:3;s:413:\"After breakfast precede towards Pahalgam Before approaching Pahalgam, you will watch in the route saffron growing fields, ruins of Awantiverman at Awantipora. Pahalgam called as &quot;Valley of Shepherds&quot; In Pahalgam Enjoy the nature &amp;amp; walk around the banks of River Lidder. Pahalgam is famous for some trekking routes also &amp;amp; is the base camp for Amaranth Pilgrimage. Overnight stay at Hotel.\";i:4;s:216:\"After breakfast check out hotel drive from Pahalgam to Aru Valley / Chandanwari/ Betaab valley (at your own cost) proceed to Srinagar. On the way you can enjoy the scenic beauty of Kashmir. On arrival check in hotel.\";i:5;s:800:\"After Breakfast visit Mughal Gardens &amp;quot;Nishat&amp;quot; (The Garden of Pleasure) and &amp;quot;Shalimar&amp;quot; (Abode of All). Drive along the Lake side on Boulevard On return visit a local Handicrafts Emporium for hand-knotted specialty silken carpets, shawls, jewellery ornaments. Also visit Shankarachariya Temple. Also see the scenic extravaganza of the Kashmir and enjoy the profusion of colors in the Paradise on Earth. While returning visit to the local crafts market and see the fine carved hand-made articles from Paper Machine &amp;amp; wood of a walnut. Evening, enjoy 01 Hour Boat Ride on Dal Lake by a gondola Boat called &quot;SHIKARA&quot; witness the ride on lake, called Venice of India &amp;amp; experience the aquatic life of Srinagar. Overnight at the Deluxe Houseboat.\";i:6;s:426:\"After breakfast, transfer towards Gulmarg, called as &quot;Meadow of Flowers&quot; Gulmarg is 150 Kms from Pahalgam at an altitude of 8700-ft. Gulmarg also referred as Meadow of Flowers is a famous Ski Resort &amp;amp; the world\'s highest 18 hole Golf Course. The place was prominent during the British time. Enjoy the scenic view of Kongdori on a Cable Car Ride – OPTIONAL (Gondola) Dinner &amp;amp; Overnight at the Hotel.\";i:7;s:466:\"After breakfast leave with full day excursion for Sonmarg. Situated at an altitude of 9000 Ft. Sonmarg – 84 Kms is also called as &quot;The meadow of gold&quot; has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. The Sindh River that meanders through the valley abounds with trout and mahaseer. Ponies can be hired for the trip up to Thajiwas glacier, which is a major local attraction during the summer. Return for Dinner &amp;amp; overnight stay Hotel.\";i:8;s:95:\"After breakfast checkout hotel and drop at Srinagar Airport. End of your tour and our services.\";}s:23:\"itinerary_content_inner\";a:8:{i:1;s:585:\"&lt;p&gt;On arrival at Jammu Airport/Railway Station you will meet and greet with our representative and derive for Katra, situated in the foothills of Trikuta Mountains where the holy shrine of Mata Vaishno Rani is located. In Katra Check in hotel, dinner and overnight stay in hotel. Day: 02) Vaishno Devi Darshan-Katra After breakfast at hotel and proceed for Darshan here you will be guided and escorted towards Mata Vaishno Devi shrine for traditional ritual and belief and fulfill your cultural chastity. After Darshan you will be back towards hotel for Overnight stay.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:2;s:280:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast at hotel and proceed for Darshan here you will be guided and escorted towards Mata Vaishno Devi shrine for traditional ritual and belief and fulfill your cultural chastity.After Darshan you will be back towards hotel for ​O​vernight stay.​&lt;/p&gt;\";i:3;s:470:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast precede towards Pahalgam Before approaching Pahalgam, you will watch in the route saffron growing fields, ruins of Awantiverman at Awantipora. Pahalgam called as &quot;Valley of Shepherds&quot; In Pahalgam Enjoy the nature &amp;amp; walk around the banks of River Lidder. Pahalgam is famous for some trekking routes also &amp;amp; is the base camp for Amaranth Pilgrimage. Overnight stay at Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:4;s:235:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast check out hotel drive from Pahalgam to Aru Valley / Chandanwari/ Betaab valley (at your own cost) proceed to Srinagar. On the way you can enjoy the scenic beauty of Kashmir. On arrival check in hotel.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:5;s:819:\"&lt;p&gt;After Breakfast visit Mughal Gardens &amp;quot;Nishat&amp;quot; (The Garden of Pleasure) and &amp;quot;Shalimar&amp;quot; (Abode of All). Drive along the Lake side on Boulevard On return visit a local Handicrafts Emporium for hand-knotted specialty silken carpets, shawls, jewellery ornaments. Also visit Shankarachariya Temple. Also see the scenic extravaganza of the Kashmir and enjoy the profusion of colors in the Paradise on Earth. While returning visit to the local crafts market and see the fine carved hand-made articles from Paper Machine &amp;amp; wood of a walnut. Evening, enjoy 01 Hour Boat Ride on Dal Lake by a gondola Boat called &quot;SHIKARA&quot; witness the ride on lake, called Venice of India &amp;amp; experience the aquatic life of Srinagar. Overnight at the Deluxe Houseboat.&lt;/p&gt;\";i:6;s:483:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast, transfer towards Gulmarg, called as &quot;Meadow of Flowers&quot; Gulmarg is 150 Kms from Pahalgam at an altitude of 8700-ft. Gulmarg also referred as Meadow of Flowers is a famous Ski Resort &amp;amp; the world\'s highest 18 hole Golf Course. The place was prominent during the British time. Enjoy the scenic view of Kongdori on a Cable Car Ride – OPTIONAL (Gondola) Dinner &amp;amp; Overnight at the Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:7;s:523:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast leave with full day excursion for Sonmarg. Situated at an altitude of 9000 Ft. Sonmarg – 84 Kms is also called as &quot;The meadow of gold&quot; has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. The Sindh River that meanders through the valley abounds with trout and mahaseer. Ponies can be hired for the trip up to Thajiwas glacier, which is a major local attraction during the summer. Return for Dinner &amp;amp; overnight stay Hotel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\";i:8;s:114:\"&lt;p&gt;After breakfast checkout hotel and drop at Srinagar Airport. End of your tour and our services.&lt;/p&gt;\";}}s:4:\"cost\";a:6:{s:14:\"includes_title\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"cost_includes\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"cost_includes_val\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"excludes_title\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"cost_excludes\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"cost_excludes_val\";s:0:\"\";}s:3:\"faq\";a:1:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}s:3:\"map\";a:2:{s:9:\"image_url\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"iframe\";s:0:\"\";}}'),
